HEADWORD: Associationist
<hw>As*so`ci*a"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Philos.)</fld>
<def>One who explains the higher functions and relations of the soul by
the association of ideas; <it>e. g.</it>, Hartley, J. C. Mill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

